   \}<\^{}>\{\{2 - \}\}\$\$\textbackslash{}end\{document\}) classified
   regional salinity as chloride-sulfate type, exhibiting significant
   spatial heterogeneity (variation coefficients: 0.37-4.04). The SVM model
   achieved optimal performance (R2 = 0.6885, lowest RMSE/MAE/MBE),
   demonstrating robust generalization and anti-overfitting capabilities
   via its Gaussian kernel. Spatial predictions from RF, BP, and OLS
   exhibited scattering, whereas SVM and ELM generated coherent
